The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 14 June is 42,758 (4,949 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 09 June, there were 259 new confirmed cases (30.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 02 June, there were 179 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 45% (80 extra cases).
